body:
Toolkit installation:
  1.1. Download and extract the “bmtool.zip” file to a folder of choice. This will create five folders: “doc”, “lib”, “mat”, “txt” and “work”;


1.2. Start MATLAB;


1.3. Add the “lib” folder to your MATLAB path \(File->Set path...->...).

Starting BMTool:
  2.1. Start MATLAB and change the current directory to the “work” folder created upon installation;


2.2. At the MATLAB command prompt, type “bmtool”. This will open the BMTool graphical user interface \(GUI) \(
